Mobile & Desktop Rules
Responsive Breakpoints (Tailwind)

base (0px+): mobile — single column, bottom nav, full-width components
md (768px+): tablet — two-column layouts appear, sidebar replaces bottom nav
lg (1024px+): desktop — full sidebar, multi-column dashboard grid
Never design for desktop first. Every component must be usable at 375px width.

Touch & Interaction

Minimum tap target: 44×44px (WCAG) — apply min-h-[44px] min-w-[44px] to all interactive elements
No hover-only affordances — anything on hover must also be accessible on long-press or secondary tap
Kanban drag-and-drop: use @dnd-kit pointer sensors (works for both mouse and touch)
Canvas workspace: use Pointer Events API (not Mouse Events) for pan/drag — enables touch support
Swipe gestures (diary log dismiss, task complete): implement with useSwipe hook using touchstart/touchend

Capacitor-Specific

Import native plugins only inside if (Capacitor.isNativePlatform()) guards
Haptic feedback on: task completion, quick log submit, drag-and-drop drop

ts  import { Haptics, ImpactStyle } from '@capacitor/haptics';
  await Haptics.impact({ style: ImpactStyle.Medium });

Pull-to-refresh on: Home Hub, Diary feed

ts  // Use @capacitor/push-notifications only after user explicitly enables in Settings

Deep links: codex:// scheme — configure in capacitor.config.ts
Status bar: dark content on light, light content on dark — set in App.tsx on mount
Safe area insets: use env(safe-area-inset-bottom) for bottom nav padding (iPhone notch)

css  padding-bottom: calc(env(safe-area-inset-bottom) + 16px);
Tauri-Specific

System tray: show unread task count badge
Global shortcut: Cmd/Ctrl+Shift+L opens QuickLogBar in a floating mini-window
Auto-launch: optional, user-controlled in Settings
Window size: remember last window size/position in Tauri store
File system access: SQLite path uses Tauri appDataDir() on desktop, not hardcoded path

AppShell Layout
tsx// Mobile: bottom nav tabs
<nav className="fixed bottom-0 left-0 right-0 flex h-16 items-center justify-around
                bg-codex-surface border-t border-codex-border
                pb-[env(safe-area-inset-bottom)] md:hidden">

// Desktop: left sidebar
<aside className="hidden md:flex md:w-16 lg:w-60 flex-col h-screen
                  bg-codex-surface border-r border-codex-border">
Network & Offline

TanStack Query's networkMode: 'offlineFirst' for all queries
Show offline banner when navigator.onLine === false
Diary QuickLogBar works offline: queue in IndexedDB, sync on reconnect (implement in Phase 2)
API base URL: VITE_API_URL env var — different values for dev/mobile/desktop builds
